column5: Figured I'd post a pic since i just figured out how these guys are all from the spring, southern Ontario creeks biggest one was 15" all caught on worm.
nice back home squaretails...I miss the naturals.
yyyuuuuuummmm..   Looks like a tasty meal.
nice size for stream fish. way to go!
Didn't even have to leave the house to catch'em.  That's a quality fishery right there dood.  lol.... nice specks.
The wife hasn't been the same at letting me out with the camera, I may have accidentally dropped it into the river while releasing a small rainbow in the past
